      "body" : "1. Sure, that case could be made. I can do it as a scoped named enum (`enum class`). Any suggestion on a proper name for that enumeration?\r\n2. The goal of this PR is to get rid of enum hacks. Changing existing `const`:s to `constexpr`:s is not within that scope :-)\r\n3. When introducing new compile-time constants I prefer `constexpr` which is explicit about the intention of the code (getting a *compile-time* constant). Do you see any compelling reasons to avoid using `constexpr` (which implies `const`) for compile-time constants?",
      "commit_id" : "1e65f0f3396d5d7eaa8e8dd3668dfa180b541c18",
      "created_at" : "2017-07-25T22:30:15Z",
